### Formula Logic Explained (Plain English)

#### **Column D: Last Week Delays**
```
IFERROR(COUNTIFS(LW_Data!$B$4:$B$3000, [Supplier Name], LW_Data!$J$4:$J$3000, "Delay"), 0)
```

**In Plain English:**
> "Count all rows in the **Last Week Data** where:
> 1. The **Supplier column (B)** matches the supplier name in this row, AND
> 2. The **On-Time/Delay column (J)** equals 'Delay'
> 
> If any error occurs, return 0 instead."

---

#### **Column E: Current Week Delays**
```
IFERROR(COUNTIFS(CW_Data!$B$4:$B$3000, [Supplier Name], CW_Data!$J$4:$J$3000, "Delay"), 0)
```

**In Plain English:**
> "Count all rows in the **Current Week Data** where:
> 1. The **Supplier column (B)** matches the supplier name in this row, AND
> 2. The **On-Time/Delay column (J)** equals 'Delay'
> 
> If any error occurs, return 0 instead."

---

#### **Column F: Delta Change (Δ)**
```
IFERROR(E[row] - D[row], 0)
```

**In Plain English:**
> "Calculate the **difference** between Current Week Delays and Last Week Delays.
> - **Positive number** = More delays this week (worse)
> - **Negative number** = Fewer delays this week (better)
> - **Zero** = No change
> 
> If any error occurs, return 0."

---

#### **Column G: Trend Indicator**
```
IF(E[row] < D[row], "✅ Improved", "🔴 Worsened")
```

**In Plain English:**
> "Compare Current Week Delays to Last Week Delays:
> - If **CW Delays < LW Delays** → Display **'✅ Improved'** (supplier got better)
> - Otherwise → Display **'🔴 Worsened'** (supplier stayed same or got worse)"

